Package: fastfocal
Type: Package
Title: Fast Focal and Multi-Scale Raster Operations with Optional 'FFT'
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Ho Yi", "Wan", email = "hoyiwan@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Fast moving-window ("focal") and buffered extraction for raster data using the 'terra' package. 
    Selects between a 'C++' backend (via the 'terra' package) and a Fast Fourier Transform ('FFT') backend 
    automatically based on problem size, with optional padding to FFT-friendly lengths. 
    Supports common window types (e.g., circle, rectangle, gaussian), summary functions 
    (mean, sum, min, max, standard deviation, median), and NA handling consistent with 'terra' 
    via 'na.rm' and 'na.policy'. Operates on 'SpatRaster' objects and returns results with the same geometry.
    Methods references: Cooley and Tukey (1965) <doi:10.1090/S0025-5718-1965-0178586-1>; 
    Hijmans (2024) "terra: Spatial Data Analysis" <https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=terra>.
